- 4 boys drop out of 14 boys, so the number of boys left is 14 - 4 = 10 boys.
- 3 girls drop out of 10 girls, so the number of girls left is 10 - 3 = 7 girls.

**Answer:**

The school has 10 boys and 7 girls left after 4 boys and 3 girls drop out.
